   pd:'0.5-1g/kg per dose orally (specialist)',pm:0,pf:'Oral 3-4 times daily or rectal',pr:'Oral/Rectal',pw:'Ion-exchange resin — binds K in gut (exchanges Ca for K). Removes K from body (unlike GIK/sodium bicarb). Onset slow (4-24h) — not acute emergency. Rectal more rapid than oral (but less convenient). Risk of intestinal necrosis (especially post-op with sorbitol — avoid sorbitol preparations). Constipation (give laxative). Newer agents: patiromer (Veltassa), sodium zirconium cyclosilicate (Lokelma) — better tolerated.',
