   pd:'Not established',pm:0,pf:'BD-TDS',pr:'Oral',pw:'Irreversible non-selective MAOI (monoamine oxidase A+B inhibitor) — increases 5-HT, NA, DA. Atypical depression (anxiety, hypersomnia, hyperphagia, leaden paralysis, rejection sensitivity — responds better than TCAs — MAOI advantage). Treatment-resistant MDD. Social anxiety (evidence). Hypertensive crisis (tyramine — cheese reaction — MAJOR diet restriction). Serotonin syndrome (drug interactions — very dangerous). Irreversible (2 weeks to recover after stopping). Washout 14 days before/after most antidepressants.',
