   pd:'Not established <18y',pm:0,pf:'100mg SC at weeks 0 and 4; then every 8 weeks',pr:'SC injection',pw:'Anti-IL-23 (p19 subunit) mAb. Plaque psoriasis (VOYAGE trials — high PASI 90/100 response rates). PsA. Unlike IL-17 inhibitors: lower candida risk; may not worsen IBD (IL-23 plays different role). Monthly then 8-weekly maintenance. Minimal drug interactions (not CYP metabolised). Infection risk. Live vaccines avoid.',
