   pd:'Anaphylaxis IM: 0.01mg/kg (max 0.5mg). Arrest IV: 10mcg/kg (neonates: 10-30mcg/kg).',pm:0,pf:'Single IM (anaphylaxis); IV bolus (arrest); IV infusion (septic shock/low cardiac output)',pr:'IM (anaphylaxis); IV (arrest/shock)',pw:'Catecholamine — alpha + beta adrenoceptor agonist. Cardiac arrest (ALS — 1mg IV every 3-5 min after 3rd shock). Anaphylaxis (IM 0.5mg — 1:1000 — mid-anterolateral thigh). Anaphylaxis treatment of choice (alpha — reverses peripheral vasodilation/hypotension; beta-1 — increases HR/contractility; beta-2 — bronchodilation). Septic shock (inotrope + vasopressor). Croup (nebulised — vasoconstriction). Haemostasis (local infiltration in surgery). Auto-injectors (EpiPen) — self-administration.',
